<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <%- include('../partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('../partials/header') %>

    <main>
        <section class="page-header">
            <div class="container">
                <h1>About Mindset.i</h1>
                <p>Change begins in one place — the individual.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- THE FOUNDATION -->
        <section class="story-section">
            <div class="story-grid">
                <div class="story-image">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1529156069898-49953e39b3ac?w=800&q=80" alt="People connecting">
                </div>
                <div class="story-text">
                    <h3>The Foundation</h3>
                    <p>Mindset.i was born from a single conviction: that all transformation begins within. Not in policy documents. Not in organisational charts. In the quiet, unguarded moment when a person looks inward and realises they were never broken — only asleep.</p>
                    <p>We are a personal development movement based in Eswatini, rooted in the belief that every human being carries within them the capacity for profound change. Our work is not to fix you. It is to remind you of what you already are.</p>
                    <p class="poetic">"All that you are looking for is at the place you are looking from."</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- THE VISION -->
        <section class="story-section">
            <div class="story-grid reverse">
                <div class="story-image">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511632765486-a01980e1a18a?w=800&q=80" alt="Community gathering">
                </div>
                <div class="story-text">
                    <h3>The Vision</h3>
                    <p>We envision an Eswatini — and ultimately an Africa — where individuals lead themselves before they lead others. Where schools are not factories of performance but gardens of presence. Where corporate teams are bound not by contracts but by shared humanity.</p>
                    <p>Our Seven Pillars are not a curriculum. They are a map back to yourself. From Repentance to Love, each pillar represents a threshold crossed, a layer shed, a truth remembered.</p>
                    <p class="poetic">"The cup was never empty. The work was never addition. It was recognition."</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- THE FOUNDER -->
        <section class="story-section">
            <div class="story-grid">
                <div class="story-image">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507003211169-0a1dd7228f2d?w=800&q=80" alt="Founder portrait">
                </div>
                <div class="story-text">
                    <h3>The Founder</h3>
                    <p>The founder of Mindset.i is a seeker first, a teacher second. With years of experience in personal development, leadership training, and organisational transformation, he has walked the path he now illuminates for others.</p>
                    <p>His approach is not academic — it is embodied. He does not speak from theory but from lived experience: the falls, the rises, the long nights of doubt, and the dawn of clarity that follows.</p>
                    <p>He believes that the most powerful thing a leader can do is to be fully human in front of other humans. Not perfect. Present.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- THE POET -->
        <section class="poet-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="poet-image">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1493225457124-a3eb161ffa5f?w=400&q=80" alt="The Poet">
                </div>
                <h3>The Poet</h3>
                <div class="role">Resident Wordsmith & Performance Artist</div>
                <p>"Where philosophy meets rhythm, where truth meets verse — that is where the poet lives. His words do not explain. They open. His performances are included in every Mindset.i engagement, at no extra charge, because we believe that art is not an add-on. It is the language of the soul."</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.85rem; opacity: 0.6;">For external private events, the poet is available at E5,000.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- THE PHILOSOPHY -->
        <section class="story-section">
            <div class="story-grid reverse">
                <div class="story-image">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517048676732-d65bc937f952?w=800&q=80" alt="Team collaboration">
                </div>
                <div class="story-text">
                    <h3>Why We Exist</h3>
                    <p>We exist because we have seen what happens when a student realises their worth is not their grade. When a teacher remembers why they chose this path. When a corporate team stops competing and starts connecting. When a graduate steps into the world not with fear, but with presence.</p>
                    <p>We do not promise easy answers. We promise honest mirrors. We promise stillness in a noisy world. We promise that the change you seek has already begun — because you are here, reading this, which means some part of you is already awake.</p>
                    <p class="poetic">"What we seek is not outside us. It is dormant within, waiting to be awakened."</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>